I'll solve this step by step to calculate the ROE, Debt to Asset Ratio, and Gross Profit Margin based on the financial statements provided.

### 1) Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = Net Profit / Total Owner's Equity
- Net Profit = $1,842,166.21
- Total Owner's Equity = $29,842,166.21
- ROE = 1,842,166.21 / 29,842,166.21 = 0.0617 = 6.17%

### 2) Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
- Total Liabilities = $1,015,922.54
- Total Assets = $30,858,088.75
- Debt to Asset Ratio = 1,015,922.54 / 30,858,088.75 = 0.0329 = 0.03

### 3) Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue
- Gross Profit = $5,718,450.67
- Total Revenue = $20,318,450.67
- Gross Profit Margin = 5,718,450.67 / 20,318,450.67 = 0.2815 = 28.15%
